						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Amṛitaghaṭēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Jaṭāvarmaṉ Parākramapāṇḍya. Year 5</p>						

						<p>On grounds of palaeography the inscription may be assigned to the 13th century.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of 150 <hi rend="italic">varāhaṉ</hi> for a perpetual lamp for god Tirukkōḍikkuḻagar in Umbaḷa-nāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Taraṇimuḻudumuḍaiya-vaḷanāḍu by Gamudavaṉ Āṇḍāṉ Peṟṟā[ṉ*].</p>						

						</summary>
